Abbey Mortgage Bank Plc has reiterated its commitment to providing modern, affordable and accessible housing finance solutions to its customers. The Managing Director/CEO of the bank, Madu Hamman, disclosed this during the launch of the Abbey Mortgage Bank Mobile App. Madu said the mobile app marked a big step in the democratization of mortgage banking in Nigeria as it provided unprecedented home ownership access for Nigerians in all geographical locations. “We are delighted to be at the forefront of digital banking within the mortgage banking space. We recognize that these are very difficult times and our customers are looking for a partner that can help them navigate the challenges induced by the COVID-19 pandemic. “This is why we are constantly raising the bar and pushing the limits in service delivery by pioneering innovative solutions that make banking easier and faster for our customers,” he said. He added that the bank is utilizing the latest technology in keeping with its commitment to simplify home ownership, provide funding to qualified customers and reduce access times. The Group Head, E-business and Support, Felix Omodayo Owotuga, said the app will provide customers with easy access to their account as well as the ability to perform transactions seamlessly without the need for in-person banking. “With over 108 million internet users in Nigeria and an estimated 120 million mobile phone holders, Abbey Mortgage is now able to connect more Nigerians to quick and professional guides towards their journey to home ownership. Customers will also be rewarded with fabulous prizes as they refer friends to the AbbeyMobile App,” he said.